Putting it all together, there are signs of file manipulation (attrib.exe), repeated powershell usage which could be for scripting malicious actions, and attempts to modify system configurations. These indicators collectively suggest possible malicious activity. While none of the individual events are conclusive on their own, the combination raises red flags.
